documents.inputText: Lanhee Chen and Jessica Tarlov discuss lawmakers who violate their own coronavirus guidelines on 'Outnumbered Overtime'We weren’t going to comment onCalifornia Gov. Gavin Newsom’sappalling hypocrisy in attending a large, raucous and maskless dinner party even as he’s ordering Golden Staters to cancel large Thanksgiving gatherings.But then he got caught tellingliesin his so-called apology.The birthday celebration was at Napa’s French Laundry, perhaps the nation’s best (and most expensive) eatery. News of it leaked just hours afterNewsompushed new guidelines discouraging get-togethers of more than three households, as California has just passed 1 million confirmed coronavirus cases.Caught gathering with his wife and people from many households — lobbyists and execs fromthe California Medical Association, no less — Newsom admitted: “I should have modeled better behavior.”But he also insisted the party dined outside. In fact, photos show a table indoors with a glass sliding door opening out on to a courtyard.What a worm.CLICK HERE TO READ THIS EDITORIAL IN THE NEW YORK POST
